13. Operational Economics

The Strike Core was intended as a validation platform rather than a commercial aircraft.

Benefits included:

Development Cost Reduction

Lower complexity reduced prototype expenses.

Maintenance Reduction

Simplified architecture reduced servicing hours.

Data Generation

Provided engineering knowledge for future platforms.

14. Evolutionary Significance

The most important contribution of the Strike Core was its role as the foundation of the Boeing 220-G lineage.

Evolution Path:

